2. InstallationTop

Before Installation

Please make sure that you have a phpBB 3.0.12 version installed.

Creating Language Folder

This point is important only if you use language other than British English (en).

  • Go to the imageset/ directory.
  • Make copy of the en/ folder.
  • Name the copy with ISO Code of your language.
  • Place copy in the imageset/ folder.

Uploading Files

Choose what colors do you want to use. Remember that every color scheme is in it own folder.
Place chosen folders in the following location on your server: 

your_phpBB3_installation/styles

For example:

public_html/phpBB3/styles

Enabling Theme

Log in to your phpBB3 administrator control panel(ACP) and go to the styles tab and click install: In the next page make this theme as the default style and click submit:

3. StructureTop

Theme Folders

There are three main folders in the theme: 

Ariki/
├── imageset/
├── template/
└── theme/

Imageset folder contains all theme images.
Template folder contains all .html and .js files.
Theme folder contains all CSS files.

4. Making ChangesTop

Applying Changes

On the default phpBB3 configuration you won't see any changes in the theme after editing theme files via FTP.
To see the changes you must refresh:

  • Templates if you modified files in the template/ folder.
  • Themes if you modified files in the theme/ folder.
  • Imagesets if you modified files in the imageset/ folder.

You can do this by selecting part of the theme that you want to refrest from the menu on the left side and clicking refresh:

Other Method

If you want to see the changes after uploading files via FTP you can turn on automatic refresh.
Just go to the administrator control panel(general tab), select load settings from menu, check to recompile stale style components and click sumbit:

5. Overall CustomizationTop

Controlling Custom Blocks

You can control custom blocks by editing template/custom_settings.html file: 

<!-- DEFINE $CUSTOM_NAVIGATION_TYPE = 1 -->
<!-- DEFINE $CUSTOM_NAVIGATION = 1 -->
<!-- DEFINE $CUSTOM_FOOTER = 1 -->
<!-- DEFINE $CUSTOM_FOOTER_BLOCKS = 1 -->
<!-- DEFINE $CUSTOM_SIDEBAR = 1 -->

$CUSTOM_NAVIGATION_TYPE can have three values 1,2 and 3 and gives you control over navigation: $CUSTOM_NAVIGATION can have two values 0 and 1(0=OFF, 1=ON) and gives you control over navigation: $CUSTOM_FOOTER can have three values 1,2 and 3 and gives you control over footer style: $CUSTOM_FOOTER_BLOCKS can have two values 0 and 1(0=OFF, 1=ON) and gives you control over footer blocks: $CUSTOM_SIDEBAR can have two values 0 and 1(0=OFF, 1=ON) and gives you control over sidebar:

Changing Logo

Your logo can have any extension that you want.
Maximum logo height is 100px.

  • Upload your logo into imageset/ folder.
  • Open imageset/imageset.cfg file.
  • Find: 
# Images
img_site_logo = site_logo.svg*26*76
  • Replace site_logo.svg with your logo file name(remember about extension).
  • Replace *26*76 with your logo height and width *height*width.

6. NavigationTop

Managing Navigation Links

Mobile and desktop navigation links are placed in the same file template/custom_navigation.html.
Example of two items in the navigation and drop down list: 

<li>
    <a href="{U_INDEX}" title="{L_INDEX}">Rules</a>
</li>
<li>
    <a href="{U_INDEX}" title="{L_INDEX}">Drop Down</a>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <a href="{U_INDEX}" title="{L_INDEX}">First Item</a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="{U_INDEX}" title="{L_INDEX}">Second Item</a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="{U_INDEX}" title="{L_INDEX}">Third Item</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</li>

Remember that template/custom_navigation.html contains only list items. Not a full list, that is the reason there is no <ul> tag for main links in this file because the list is already within this tag.

7. SidebarTop

Managing Sidebar Blocks

Sidebar content is placed in the template/custom_sidebar.html file.
Copy this example into file mentioned above and replace text with your: 

<div class="mono-block">
    <div class="mono-block-header">

        Block title here

    </div>

    <div class="mono-block-content">

        Block content here

    </div>
</div>

You can place unlimited amount of block in the sidebar.

8. Footer BlocksTop

Managing Footer Blocks

Every footer blocks are placed in the same file: template/custom_footer_blocks.html.
Standard footer block with full width look like this: 

<div>
    <h3>

        Block title here

    </h3>
    <p>
        
        Block content here

    </p>
</div>

You can delete block title if you want: 

<div>
    <p>
        
        Block content here

    </p>
</div>

Footer block must be placed inside two following blocks: 

<div class="wrap" id="custom-footer">
<div class="c-wrap">

    Footer blocks here

</div>
</div>

Footer Blocks Grid

Footer can have up to 10 columns.
Replace the class_goes_here, according to number of columns that you want to have: 

<div class="class_goes_here">
    <p>
        
        Block content here

    </p>
</div>

Below you can find class names for a specific number of columns(for replacing with class_goes_here):

c2-5

c7-5

c5
